cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision, specifically illuminant estimation using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel framework for learning a sensor-independent working space, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence and deep learning, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image and video processing, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of camera sensors, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
